	doi = {10.1117/12.2233366},
	abstract = {A physical model of the Point Spread Function (PSF) utilizing the Wavefront sensing and the Active Optics System (AOS) of the Dark Energy Camera (DECam) at the CTIO 4-meter Blanco telescope is described. Stars measured from out-of-focus exposures are individually ﬁt to a pupil plane Zernike expansion to create a physical model for the optical system. This model is reﬁned with measurements of the second moments of the PSF to account for per-exposure camera misalignments and primary mirror ﬁgure error, and which are compared directly to those determined by the AOS. Comparison of the physical model to the observed data are shown, and the eﬀects of atmosphere on the measurement of the Zernike expansion are presented.},
